    "panel-3": {
      "kind": "Panel",
      "spec": {
        "data": {
          "kind": "QueryGroup",
          "spec": {
            "queries": [],
            "queryOptions": {},
            "transformations": []
          }
        },
        "description": "Note that `Scrape job` names from this panel and `Job` names from the `Targets status` panel do not always match 1:1. The `Scrape job` names might sometime be overriden in the ServiceMonitor or PodMonitor (e.g. `jobLabel` field, relabeling, etc...), a ServiceMonitor or PodMonitor might also target multiple endpoints which results in multiple endpoints (kubelet, cadvisor, probes), all being aggregated into a single job.",
        "id": 3,
        "links": [],
        "title": "",
        "vizConfig": {
          "group": "text",
          "kind": "VizConfig",
          "spec": {
            "fieldConfig": {
              "defaults": {},
              "overrides": []
            },
            "options": {
              "code": {
                "language": "plaintext",
                "showLineNumbers": false,
                "showMiniMap": false
              },
              "content": "#### Targets discovery\n\nEach line in this panel shows how many targets where found per ServiceMonitor or PodMonitor. When the value is **0** it means that no targets where found and the corresponding application is therefore not being monitored. This is likely a problem with the label selectors used in the ServiceMonitor or PodMonitor which needs to be fixed.\n\n ",
              "mode": "markdown"
            }
          },
          "version": "13.1.0-local"
        }
      }
    },
